{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":19524,"record_hash":"sha256:d7de06d26f51232172a958755ed4559c76b2be50e0ebc9f76f795afe96e909bf","timestamp":"2026-05-10T10:43:38.860Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Yeah, I think your discomfort is pointing at a real API gap.\n\nRight now GitMeta exposes a low-level key/value API:\n\n```rust\nhandle.set(\"some:key\", value)?;\nhandle.set_add(\"some:set\", value)?;\nhandle.list_push(\"some:list\", value)?;\n```\n\nThat is flexible, but it pushes all schema ownership onto callers. So every caller ends up inventing string constants, prefix helpers, and little write loops. That’s why our code keeps oscillating between “too stringly” and “too ceremonial.”\n\nThe API I’d want from GitMeta is probably an optional typed layer on top of the primitive API, not a replacement for it:\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Serialize)]\n#[serde(rename_all = \"kebab-case\")]\nstruct SourceMetadata {\n    agent: String,\n    provider: Option<String>,\n    model: Option<String>,\n    tool_version: Option<String>,\n}\n\nhandle.set_fields(source_prefix, &source_metadata)?;\n```\n\nWhere GitMeta would:\n- use serde field names / `rename` attributes as key suffixes\n- skip `None`\n- convert simple scalar values to `MetaValue`\n- write `prefix:<field-name>` for each field\n\nThen our code could say “persist this metadata struct under this prefix” instead of spelling out every field key. For sets/lists, I’d still keep explicit calls like `set_add` and `list_push`, because those are operations, not plain struct fields.\n\nSo yes: I think the library could use a small typed-field helper. For this POC, I’d be cautious about building that abstraction locally unless it clearly makes the code better. But as feedback for `git-meta`, this is a solid direction: keep the raw API, add a serde-backed “write fields under prefix” API for structured metadata.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-10T10:43:38.860Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}